ross section of texts (including conduct books and treatises, travel writing and wonder books) is comparative, putting canonical European authors such as Castiglione into dialogue with transatlantic and Anglo-Ottoman literary exchange.  aDescription based on information from publisher. 0aPeople with disabilitiesxSocial aspectsyEarly modern, 1500-1700. 0aHuman bodyxSocial aspectsyEarly modern, 1500-1700. 0aPeople with disabilities in literature. 0aPeople with disabilities in art. 4aElectronic books.22aMichigan Publishing (University of Michigan)eissuing body. 0aCorporealities.40zAccess to the Michigan Publishing online version:uhttps://doi.org/10.3998/mpub.10014355